ingredientLines: 2/3 cups all-purpose flour, plus up to another ¼ - ½ cup for kneading
¼ teaspoon baking soda (to counteract acidity in the wine, which could affect the yeast)
2 medium yellow onions, cut on the vertical axis and then thinly sliced crosswise
3 cloves garlic, peeled and thinly sliced
1 cup sun-dried tomatoes in oil, well drained, and coarsely chopped
4 ounces fresh basil leaves (1 cup after chopping coarsely)
4 ounces chorizo, cut into 1/2 inch dice
10 or 12 kalamata olives, pitted and halved
½ cup grated manchego or iberico cheese
